name:     In Depth    2024 European elections: Who is running in France? France will vote on June 9  to elect 81 members of the European Parliament, as the 27 member states of the European Union renew the assembly's 720 seats. 
content:Val√©rie Hayer will lead the European elections campaign for President Emmanuel Macron's party Renaissance and its allies Horizons and MoDem, it was confirmed on Thursday, February 24.With Hayer, who has served as MEP since 2019, the roster for the 2024 elections is almost complete: All the major parties have named a top candidate to lead their campaign. Seats will be allocated proportionally to each party's score, with a minimum threshold of 5% of the vote required to obtain seats.